  "response_text": "The commercial opens with a driver’s-eye view of a narrow, wet two-lane road winding through a dense forest. The image is misty and soft-edged, with dark trees crowding both sides and pale fog hanging over the road. Yellow center lines curve ahead, and the glossy pavement reflects the dim light. The road bends through tall trunks and overhanging branches, first in a shadowy, bluish haze and then into warmer patches of light, as if moving quickly through a damp wooded area.\n\nThe forest road continues to twist and climb. The trees thin slightly, and shafts of pale light appear through the mist. The road surface remains slick and reflective, with reddish-brown leaves or earth along the shoulders. The view follows the yellow center lines around curves, past tall, straight trunks, then into a clearer stretch where the forest gives way to a brighter sky. The atmosphere shifts from foggy and enclosed to more open and sunlit.\n\nThe roadway then rises toward a bright horizon between dark rows of trees. The sun glows low on the left, and the wet pavement shines with a golden reflection. The scene moves uphill, leaving the deep forest behind. A brief close view of the double yellow center lines fills the image, then the road appears again along a hillside, with dark evergreens on the left and dry golden grass sloping down on the right under a clear blue sky.\n\nAs the hillside road continues, the image gradually reveals that this traveling landscape is being displayed on a computer screen. A gray Macintosh-style desktop surrounds the road image, which sits inside a rectangular window near the upper left of the monitor. Along the top is a pale menu bar with small, mostly unreadable text. To the right is another window filled with a grid of small numbers or data cells, like a spreadsheet. Below, a separate window shows a colorful three-dimensional surface chart or terrain-like graph, with a vertical color scale beside it.\n\nThe wider view shows the computer setup in a dim professional workspace. On the left of the monitor stands a beige vertical Macintosh Quadra tower, with a dark vertical disk slot, small ventilation holes, a tiny indicator light, and a small rainbow Apple logo on the front. The large monitor sits to its right, its black frame surrounding the gray desktop full of overlapping windows. In the right foreground, an adult person is seen from behind, mostly in silhouette, with short dark hair and a dark top, seated close to the screen and facing the computer. Their hand rests near the keyboard or mouse area, suggesting they are operating the system while the road footage and data graphics remain visible on the display.\n\nThe road image inside the main window continues to change, showing the golden hillside and dark tree line sliding across the window, while the data grid and 3D graph remain open beside and below it. The beige Quadra tower stays prominently visible at the left, paired with the active monitor, presenting the computer as a workstation handling video-like imagery, numerical information, and visual graphics at the same time.",
